- Hypothesis: a fail-soft, fire-and-forget OTLP/HTTP JSON emitter
  built on the existing http-post-with-timeout helper is sufficient
  to give guile-sage observability parity with Claude Code on the
  same NexusHive dashboard, without pulling in protobuf or gRPC.

## Validation
- Hand-crafted JSON POST to infra-host:4318/v1/metrics returns 200 with
  partialSuccess:{} (full success). Prometheus query for
  guile_sage_session_count_total returns the expected series.
- json-write-string handles the nested alist+vector shape correctly
  (vectors -> JSON arrays, alists -> JSON objects).
- Cumulative counters survive multiple flushes (the collector
  treats subsequent flushes as the same series, not new ones)
- The unit suffix derivation works as the spec describes:
  unit=\"tokens\" -> _tokens_total, unit=\"s\" -> _seconds_total,
  unit=\"USD\" -> _USD_total, unit=\"1\" -> _total

## Refutation / known limits
- We assume the collector is on the LAN with no auth. Cloud OTel
  endpoints requiring an API key would need a header injection.
- Single-thread emission only. If sage ever goes multi-threaded the
  *counters* hash needs a mutex.
- No support for histogram or gauge metric types yet (only sum).
- The flush is synchronous and blocks the REPL for the round-trip
  latency. On the LAN this is ~10-20ms; for cloud collectors it
  could be noticeable.

